en_585748_0	Colombo (News1st) – A Prison official, who was arrested yesterday attempting to smuggle Heroin into the Welikada Prison, has been interdicted.
en_585748_1	Prisons spokesperson Thushara Upuldeniya said a special investigation has been launched into the incident.
en_585748_2	A Prisons Sergeant was arrested last afternoon for attempting smuggle 20 grams of heroin into the Welikada Prison.
en_585748_3	The Ministry of Justice and Prison Reforms said the suspect was searched when he entered the premises as prison officials were suspicious about his conduct.
en_585748_4	Prison officials also found Rs.
en_585748_5	85,000 in cash in the suspect’s possession as well as two mobile phones.
